    <tags>keyviz keystroke keypress mouse visualizer presentation FOSS embedded</tags>
    <summary>Visualize your keystrokes and mouse actions</summary>
    <description>Keyviz is a **free and open-source** tool that visualizes your keypresses and mouse actions in real-time. Let your audience know what handy shortcuts you're pressing during tutorials, presentations, collaborations, or whenever you need.

## ⌨️ Keypress and 🖱️ Mouse Actions
Along with normal keys, you can also visualize mouse actions like `CMD` + `Click`, `ALT` + `Drag`, etc.
![Keystroke Visualization](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/mulaRahul/keyviz@9ba77af6f27aa9ceb579361fb9357d625a9c0e8c/previews/visualization.png)
Display mouse clicks and scroll wheel movements alongside your cursor.
![Mouse Indicator](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/mulaRahul/keyviz@9ba77af6f27aa9ceb579361fb9357d625a9c0e8c/previews/mouse-indicator.gif)

## ⚙️ Full Customization
Don't settle for defaults. Every aspect of the visualization is under your control:
- **Styling:** Change colors (modifier vs. regular keys), size, layout, border, and background.
- **Filtering:** Control which keys are shown using hotkey or custom filters.
- **History:** Keep a visual trail of your recent inputs.
- **Position:** Move the visualization to any part of your screen.
- **Animations:** Customize how inputs appear and disappear with preset entry and exit animations.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/mulaRahul/keyviz/releases</releaseNotes>
    <!-- =============================== -->
  </metadata>
